1. Explain the CSS “box model” and the layout components that it consists of. Provide some usage examples.

2. Explain what elements will match each of the following CSS selectors:
	div, p
	div p
	div > p
	div + p
	div ~ p

3. Explain the meaning of each of these CSS units for expressing length:
	cm
	em
	in
	mm
	pc
	pt
	px

4. In CSS3, how would you select:
	Every <a> element whose href attribute value begins with “https”.
	Every <a> element whose href attribute value ends with “.pdf”.
	Every <a> element whose href attribute value contains the substring “css”.

5. Given the following HTML:

		<div id="page">
		  <h1>Heading Title</h1>
		  <h2>Subheading Title</h2>
		  <h2>Subheading Title</h2>
		  <h1>Heading Title</h1>
		  <h2>Subheading Title</h2>
		  <h1>Heading Title</h1>
		</div>
		How could you use CSS to achieve the following automatic numbering:

		1) Heading Title
		1.1) Subheading Title
		1.2) Subheading Title

		2) Heading Title
		2.1) Subheading Title



























3) Heading Title